.TH "vga_switcheroo_register_client" 9 "vga_switcheroo_register_client" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vga_switcheroo_register_client \- register vga client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vga_switcheroo_register_client
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct vga_switcheroo_client_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "bool driver_power_control "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
client pci device
.IP "ops" 12
client callbacks
.IP "driver_power_control" 12
whether power state is controlled by the driver's
runtime pm
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register vga client (GPU). Enable vga_switcheroo if another GPU and a
handler have already registered. The power state of the client is assumed
to be ON. Beforehand, \fBvga_switcheroo_client_probe_defer\fP shall be called
to ensure that all prerequisites are met.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -ENOMEM on memory allocation error.
